l wear during the numerous physical training sessions that await them  They were handed another dose of reality   You have the anticipation when you get your gym dyke  but it gets really  really gut wrenchingly real when you hear the words   Rats  meet your cadre  That s when your whole life just changes  Now calling 301 310  301 310  The anonymous voice was cut off as the door to Cameron Hall slammed shut  The buildings across the street loomed menacingly over the new cadets  and a wide range of emotions worked their way through the group  Some were eager  chomping at the bit for the invitation to join their companies  Some were a bit nervous  and others were downright terrified  And at some point during Matriculation Day  almost all of them probably second guessed their decisions to attend VMI  For those  cadets who have gone before offered a bit of advice   Stay the course  said Ranger   It s going to get hard  even for the most mentally and physically tough people here  They are going to do everything they can to break you down   Let them break you down  Let them build you into this model VMI cadet  That person is going to be great  and you are going to do great things  Don t give up on yourself and don t give up on your Brother Rats   I was having a pretty rough time last year  admitted Loken   I had one teacher  Maj   Jessica  Libertini  who said something that resonated with me  She said   All VMI is going to do is add to your character  You ll always be you   VMI  is going to give you so much more   Remember that  he advised the new cadets   Remember you are going to gain so much for coming here  even if you don t realize it  I didn t  but I am a stronger person for  coming here    Chris Floyd  VMI      I Felt Like John Hancock  Cadets Recall Signing the Matriculation Book as 495 New Cadets Sign    Cadets from each company s cadre circle the Parade Ground  shouting cadence to motivate the incoming rats  For a few more days  watch the Welcome Ceremony webcast at www vmi edu livestream  The DVD will be available for purchase at www vmi edu videos  LEXINGTON  Va  Aug  22  2015   The first thing one might have noticed at Cameron Hall Saturday morning as the new cadets gathered at VMI for Matriculation Day 2015 was the sound  With the hundreds of people   new cadets  parents  faculty  and staff   seemingly all speaking at once  their collective voices became a low drone  like the buzzing of bees  and understanding what any one individual had to say was next to impossible  But one voice rang loud and clear  anonymously belting his invitation over the public address system  Matriculation by the Numbers Total  495 In State  302 Out of State  193 Males  442 Females      53 STEM Major  63 4  Liberal Arts Majors  36 6  States Represented      31 Foreign Countries      5   Now calling 131 140  131 140  Each new number set was the signal for new cadets falling in that range  their names  numbers  and companies spelled out on placards attached to their shirts  to head to the floor  Thus  the 495 new cadets got their first taste of VMI creating order out of chaos   It s nerve wracking  but it s also exciting  said Kayla Ranger  18  Company G s lead EMT  as she recalled her Matriculation Day   It gets really real  really fast   I remember standing right there at that Marine Corps table and getting scared out of my mind  added Connor Loken  17  the team lead EMT for Company I   It s weird because these guys don t know what s coming  At the bottom of the stairs  families were met by admissions office staff  and with the drone becoming louder as more and more people filed into the facility  new cadets weaved their way through a maze of important tables   the commandant s office  financial aid  the comptroller and  finally  the registrar  Now calling 141 150  141 150  It was at the registrar s table that reality hit  Oh  parents were proud  parading around the Cameron Hall floor with their newly purchased VMI garb  So were siblings  many 